OL,3,CMassachusetts governor 'legalises'
OL,4,Chaggis in symbolic nod to Scotland fans
OL,6,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,F"We are leading a campaign to Make
OL,12,FHaggis Legal Again. C'mon, Scotland,
OL,13,FNO HAGGIS. NO PARTY," Simon Howie, the
OL,14,Fcreator of the petition, wrote at the
OL,15,Ftime.
OL,17,FGovernor Healey also praised how
OL,18,FScottish fans had brought "such joy
OL,19,Fand such energy" to Boston since their
OL,20,Ffirst game in the city against Haiti
OL,21,Fon June 13, which they won.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31005
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1781853482
OL,3,CMassachusetts governor 'legalises'
OL,4,Chaggis in symbolic nod to Scotland fans
OL,6,F"This is a time in our world right
OL,7,Fnow, people need that positivity, they
OL,8,Fneed to see that," Healey told
OL,9,FMcIntosh. "I think that's what people
OL,10,Fhere are going to associate with
OL,11,FScotland."
OL,13,FScotland play their second game
OL,14,Fagainst Morocco in Boston on Friday
OL,15,Fevening, before heading to Miami for
OL,16,Ftheir final group match against Brazil.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
