OL,3,CMassachusetts governor 'legalises'
OL,4,Chaggis in symbolic nod to Scotland fans
OL,6,FIt is Scotland's first World Cup in 28
OL,7,Fyears, and fans have been dominating
OL,8,Fthe streets of Boston, singing
OL,9,Ffootball chants, drinking the Scottish
OL,10,Fcarbonated soft drink Irn-Bru, and
OL,11,Fputting orange traffic cones on many
OL,12,Fof the city's statues.
OL,14,FThe country is currently at the top of
OL,15,FGroup C after beating Haiti, which was
OL,16,Falso the first time they have won a
OL,17,FWorld Cup game in 36 years.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/6
